%a{ name: 'key_details'}
%h2 Key details
%p This website privacy policy describes how OSM Extender protects and makes use of the information you give when you use this website.
%p If you are asked to provide information when using this website, it will only be used in the ways described in this privacy policy.
%p
  This policy is updated from time to time. The latest version is published on this page.
  This website privacy policy was updated on <b>30th Oct 2019</b>.
%p If you have any questions about this policy, please use the #{link_to('contact form', contact_us_path).html_safe}.
%p I gather and use certain information about individuals in order to provide products and services and to enable certain functions on this website. I also collect information to better understand how visitors use this website and to present timely, relevant information to them.
%p I also process information about other individuals on your behalf and at your request, you remain controller of this information.
%p I do not use automated decision making or profiling.
%p Your data is mostly being processed under the lawful basis of consent, this means that you have the right to:
%ul
  %li Informed - You are currently reading the privacy policy which addresses this.
  %li Erasure - If you would like your data erased then sign in, go to "#{ link_to "My account", my_account_path}" then click "#{link_to "Delete account", confirm_delete_my_account_path}" and follow the instructions. Please note that this deletes your data from the database and after a few months from all backups, if you require a more immediate/thorough erasure then please signin and use the #{link_to 'contact form', contact_us_path}.
  %li Access and Data Portability - If you would like a copy of your data signin and use the #{link_to 'contact form', contact_us_path}.
  %li Rectification - If you would like your data corrected then please signin in and goto your page, if you can't find where to correct the wrong information then use the #{link_to 'contact form', contact_us_path}.
  %li Lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office - #{link_to 'https://ico.org.uk', 'https://ico.org.uk'}.
%p
  Additionally some of your data is processed under the lawful basis of legitimate interests. This grants you only the right to data portability but covers no data over and above what is described elsewhere.
  This basis is used to send certain emails about significant events, for example if a security incident happens it is in the legitimate interests of OSM Extender to limit the potential issues at OSM Extender and/or potentially your legitimate interests too.

